key_points: Gabby Petito, a 22-year-old woman, went missing during a cross-country road trip with her fiancé, Brian Laundrie.
The FBI announced the discovery of a body in Wyoming believed to be Gabby's.
Joseph Petito, Gabby's father, shared a tribute to her on social media, stating 'she touched the world'.
Gabby and Laundrie embarked on their trip from Florida to New York and then headed west, documenting their journey.
Communication with Gabby ceased in late August while she was in Grand Teton National Park.
Laundrie returned to his parents' home in Florida without Gabby on Sept. 1, and she was reported missing 10 days later.
Laundrie was named a person of interest and allegedly did not cooperate with investigators.
Gabby's disappearance and the subsequent investigation attracted nationwide attention.
Joseph Petito remembered Gabby as 'amazing', 'artistic', and a 'flower child' in an interview with PEOPLE.
The FBI is conducting a full forensic analysis to determine the cause of death and encourages the public to submit any information regarding the case.
